onk (0.4) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Improve the manual pages:
    + Improve wording.
    + Fix typos.
    + Use the YYYY-MM-DD date format.
    + Remove the “AUTHOR” and “COPYRIGHT” sections.
    + Rename “USAGE EXAMPLE” sections as “EXAMPLE”.
    + Make the examples more portable.
    + Use the YYYY-MM-DD date format in the manual page.
  * Improve the build system:
    + Honour CC, CFLAGS and LDLIBS variables from environment.
    + Disable network access for xsltproc.
    + Don't use non-portable constructs for sed(1).
    + Add the “install” target.
    + Move documentation building code to a separate makefile.
  * Get rid of duplicates in the key table.
  * Relicense to the Expat license.
  * Fix compatibility with Linux ≥ 4.4.
  * Fix potential out-of-bounds read in keysniff.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Tue, 12 Sep 2017 11:08:14 +0200

